<h1>Privacy Policy</h1>

Date: 01.01.2017.
This Privacy Policy relates to DataMind service that our company provides to advertisers, publishers and content providers. The Policy came into affect on the 1th January 2017.

<h1>Personally Identifiable Information</h1>

DataMind respects the privacy of internet users. We consider protection of consumer privacy our priority. We do not collect, process or otherwise use any personal information in DataMind. We never sell or rent any personal information collected from you to any third party and will not buy or otherwise accept any personal information from any third party.

Personal information may be disclosed to judicial or other government agencies subject to warrants, subpoenas, or other governmental orders.

We do collect, process and aggregate anonymous Non-­Personally Identifiable Information (non-PII). This information is used to help our partners deliver relevant ads and content to consumers.

<h1>Children</h1>

We do not intentionally collect information from persons under the age of 13.
We do not have segments targeted at children under 13 years of age.

<h1>How and what we collect as non-PII data</h1>

<lu>

<li>A cookie, also known as an HTTP cookie, web cookie, or browser cookie, is a small piece of data sent from a website and stored in a user's web browser while the user is browsing that website. Every time the user loads the website, the browser sends the cookie back to the server to notify the website of the user's previous activity.
</li>

<li>Like most websites in the internet our company uses cookies to enhance experience for users. For example not to show the same ad again, when it is not relevant any more. In other words, we want to make internet usage more comfortable by showing content that is interesting and relevant for the user.
</li>

<li>
	We do not use any Flash cookies/LSOs (HTTP/browser cookies only).
</li>

<li>DataMind provides service for advertisers, publishers and content providers by using cookie targeting technique. To collect data we use “pixel tags” on 3rd party websites. This tags are image or javascript html tags that makes possible to operate with users cookies.
</li>

<li>
We do not collect any impression-level data through the ad that will be used for subsequent ad targeting.
</li>

<li>
We do not conduct hyperlocal geo-targeting (especially with mobile ads via GPS) and We do not collect any user's geo data.
</li>

<li>
We do not use IP for anything but for geo-targeting only.
</li>

<li>
We do not conduct browser packet-sniffing (Reading packets of information from the HTTP request).
</li>

<li>
We do not perform browser/device fingerprinting.
</li>

<li>Most of our applications use datamind.ru domain. Be aware, that part of our service (pixels) could be located on 3rd party websites. In this case this websites could collect and process your data as well.
</li>

<li>DataMind may not be responsible for such 3rd party websites and their data collection practice. Although we do select partners carefully we encourage you to carefully read terms of service and privacy policies of all websites you visit especially those where you are requested to submit personal data.
</li>
</lu>
<h1>Information sharing</h1>

Collected data is processed into targeting data segments and then used by advertisers, publishers and content providers to enhance users experience. DataMind could share collected and processed data with partners, based on that collected information could be used for third party advertising purpose. To make it possible we share non-PII with our partners. If you don’t want us to collect and process your data please use opt-out link.

<h1>Opt Out</h1>

If you want to opt out from DataMind service please use this opt-out <a href="index.html">link</a>.
It’s important to mention that you will still receive advertisements and content, but these content and advertisements will not be relevant to you. Because of technical limitations we could opt out only current browser, that’s why if you want to opt out from all devices and browsers you should repeat this procedure. If you delete all your cookies, you'll have to repeat the opt-out procedure within your respective browser.

</br>
We are also using an Advertising IDs for mobile targeting and you can use the following manuals for an opt-out purpose:
<lu>
<li>
for iOS users: <a href="https://support.apple.com/en-us/HT202074">https://support.apple.com/en-us/HT202074</a>
</li>
<li>
for Android users: <a href="https://support.google.com/ads/answer/2662922?hl=en">https://support.google.com/ads/answer/2662922?hl=en</a>
